	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I just finished this quest tonight, and thought i would post some info on werewolves and their most common locations.<BR>
Firstly, there seem to be two different levels (three if you count the ones in Mistmoore) of werewolves. The ones which spawn in Kithicor forest and the West Common Lands are of a much lower level than the ones which spawn in West Karana, which are in turn of a lower lever than those in Mistmoor. The west karana ww's are level 25. There is no variation on this _in the west karana zone_. They hit for up to 50 or so damage, and are tough for their level, my 28 ranger still can't just melee it out with these doggies. They spawn at night (the only exception to this being in kithicor forest), and unless engaged battle, will despawn at 6am. WW's in West Karana will spawn at night in two main locations. The first location is, as stated by others, near the guard house close to the qeynos hills zone. The second is near the river, close to the north karana zone. West Karana is the only place (apart from mistmoor obviously) where they will spawn consistently every night. <BR>
The other main place for werewolves to spawn (lower lvl and much easier than the karana variety) is West commons, around the lake at night. These ones do not spawn every night, it seems to be largely random, with various undead as the place holders. If you run around the lake madly killing every skeleton/zombie/mummy in sight, you might be lucky enough to get one to pop.<BR>
Ocassionally a werewolf will spawn in Kithicor forest during the early morning, but it's too rare to try camping it. <BR>
There is also a named werewolf, Grimtooth, in North Karana, again too rare to bother camping just for the claws.<BR>
South Karana I believe also has one very rare ww, the night version of Senty Alechin. <BR>
Mistmoore i know nothing about, so *shrug*<BR>
I've killed about 30 werewolves around norrath, and only received one pair of claws.<BR>
Good luck guys.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
