				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Welp I will try to clear up a few things that I know are 100% correct as of the time of this post in my own experience and not rumor.  #1) Karg may have a specific path but it's a very long one and detailed one.  Because I have seen him everywhere and I mean EVERYWHERE out in the tundra of everfrost.  Yes he is hard to get a hold of because he is killed for his loot almost as soon as he's spawned.  Although I did see him last 4 hours once because it was off hours.  #2)  I have been to all of the above zones countless times and never seen a werewolf other than in West Karana.  This does not mean they don't exist in other zones, just speaking from my own personal experience.  Werewolves at one time may have been lvl20ish but they sure arent anymore, I would say 25ish.  I killed my first one at level 30 but keep in mind I am a shaman (no snare, no pet, weak dd's, and they have sow), it was a tough fight.  I have killed 4 of them and only got one set of claws.  Don't know if that's lucky for me or not, rarity of any drop is a hard thing to guage unless you've killed 1000 of whatever and kept track of drops.  They still give me exp at 36 but are much easier to kill solo.  They have approximately 1k hitpoints.  That is just a rough estimate.  #3)  I personally have never seen these for sale or seen a pair on anybody on the Cazic Thule server.  This does not mean they don't exist cuz I&quot;m sure there are many of them, but have not a clue what to sell these for.  So given that, they seem pretty rare to me. Servers are VERY different in economies so ask around and keep your eyes peeled in the auctions.  In closing, I personally would not even attempt to camp for these.  You could level 20 times before you get the claws or get them first thing.  BUT if you are going to camp them just sit and the qhills zone of WK cuz the newbies zone it (or try to) most of the time.  So i would assume it spawns somewhere in between the zone and guard tower cuz thats the only place ive ever seen it.  And one last thing, it only spawns at night.  Sorry for such a long post just wanted to be perfectly clear.<BR>
<BR>
Xanthor Icefist<BR>
Cazic Thule
